        UC Santa Cruz Maps Coastal Flooding With NVIDIA Accelerated Computing
    </h3>

        
    <div class="cmp-teaser__description">
    	
       		<p>UC Santa Cruz Center for Coastal Climate Resilience focuses on modeling and mapping the benefits of coral reefs and mangroves for reducing flood risk, which helps inform adaptation and preservation efforts. The center uses NVIDIA CUDA-X™ software, including the cuPyNumeric library and nvfortran compiler, running on NVIDIA RTX™ GPUs awarded through the NVIDIA Academic Grant Program.</p>
        
