    </h3>

        
    <div class="cmp-teaser__description">
    	
       		<p>NUS researchers developed CondensNet, a neural network that fixes a key instability in hybrid AI-physics climate models. By correcting water vapor oversaturation during condensation, the model enables decade-long climate simulations that stay physically accurate, which is a long-standing challenge in the field.</p>
        
    </div>

        
	
	
	
